        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 28 at 6:28PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 627 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 4 miles
southwest of Altus. This thunderstorm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects.

Locations in or near the path include...
Altus...                          Wiederkehr Village...
Denning...                        Etna...
Alix...                           Meg...

This includes Interstate 40 in Arkansas between mile markers 41 and
42.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
